description: Artists, discover your perfect haven in Live/Work Loft #62, a bright 6th-floor unit in a historic 1898 Boston Wharf building in the Seaport area. Designed for practicing artists, this loft is part of a limited-equity artist cooperative, offering affordable living within a creative community. With 12-foot ceilings and original details, the loft boasts large arched windows with views of South Boston and the Blue Hills. Features include a spacious kitchen with an island, in-unit laundry, and ample closet space with loft storage. The versatile layout includes bamboo floors and a concrete studio floor, one bedroom plus a flexible sleeping alcove. Enjoy the rooftop deck's stunning views of Boston Harbor. Easily access South Station, Logan Airport, and cultural attractions. This is your chance to live and create in a historic, artistic setting in Boston. ***Must be a practicing artist , co-op board approval required and must be the primary residence.
